{"copyright": {"licenseType": "NO", "determinationType": "OTHER", "thirdPartyContentCondition": "NOT_SET"}, "subjectCategories": ["Systems Analysis and Operations Research"], "keywords": ["software analysis"], "exportControl": {"isExportControl": "NO", "ear": "NO", "itar": "NO"}, "distributionDate": "2019-07-12T00:00:00.0000000+00:00", "title": "Logic Model Checking of Time-Periodic Real-Time Systems", "stiType": "CONFERENCE_PAPER", "distribution": "PUBLIC", "submittedDate": "2015-05-26T15:37:43.3730000+00:00", "authorAffiliations": [{"sequence": 0, "submissionId": 20150008744, "meta": {"author": {"name": "Florian, Mihai"}, "organization": {"name": "Jet Propulsion Lab., California Inst. of Tech.", "location": "Pasadena, CA, United States"}}, "id": "67263fbfd81d48f49de2912bdb25fb0f"}, {"sequence": 1, "submissionId": 20150008744, "meta": {"author": {"name": "Gamble, Ed"}, "organization": {"name": "Jet Propulsion Lab., California Inst. of Tech.", "location": "Pasadena, CA, United States"}}, "id": "d0a9772d13d44d3e9ed28628afb74252"}, {"sequence": 2, "submissionId": 20150008744, "meta": {"author": {"name": "Holzmann, Gerard"}, "organization": {"name": "Jet Propulsion Lab., California Inst. of Tech.", "location": "Pasadena, CA, United States"}}, "id": "8cee5b7423f742b599ab7ce9363adaf2"}], "stiTypeDetails": "Conference Paper", "technicalReviewType": "TECHNICAL_REVIEW_TYPE_NONE", "id": 20150008744, "sourceIdentifiers": [{"number": "hdl:2014/44963", "type": "HANDLE"}], "created": "2015-05-26T15:37:43.3730000+00:00", "center": {"code": "JPL", "name": "Jet Propulsion Laboratory", "id": "efbc9c123a0f47caafa95d99b7d2e1a1"}, "onlyAbstract": false, "sensitiveInformation": 2, "abstract": "In this paper we report on the work we performed to extend the logic model checker SPIN with built-in support for the verification of periodic, real-time embedded software systems, as commonly used in aircraft, automobiles, and spacecraft. We first extended the SPIN verification algorithms to model priority based scheduling policies. Next, we added a library to support the modeling of periodic tasks. This library was used in a recent application of the SPIN model checker to verify the engine control software of an automobile, to study the feasibility of software triggers for unintended acceleration events.", "isLessonsLearned": false, "disseminated": "METADATA_ONLY", "meetings": [{"country": "United States", "submissionId": 20150008744, "endDate": "2012-06-21T00:00:00.0000000+00:00", "sponsors": [{"meta": {"organization": {"name": "American Inst. of Aeronautics and Astronautics", "location": "Reston, VA, United States"}}, "meetingId": "f60c9600253a441c850d8ab2ba499bf3", "id": "69cc3e174bf74b16af3cabb391e0ac1e"}], "name": "AIAA Infotech @ Aerospace 2012 Conference", "location": "Garden Grove, CA", "id": "f60c9600253a441c850d8ab2ba499bf3", "startDate": "2012-06-19T00:00:00.0000000+00:00"}], "publications": [{"submissionId": 20150008744, "id": "76bc0932582f4510b5faf0b9bd89a243", "publicationDate": "2012-06-19T00:00:00.0000000+00:00"}], "status": "CURATED", "related": [], "downloads": [], "downloadsAvailable": false, "index": "submissions-2022-09-30-06-07"}